         <div type="entry">
                <head>Aḥudemmeh of Balad</head>
                <ab type="idnos">
                    <idno type="URI">https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Ahudemmeh-of-Balad</idno>
                    <idno type="syriaca-bibl">http://syriaca.org/bibl/34</idno>
                    <idno type="entry">25</idno>
                    <milestone unit="pages" n="13"/>
                    <idno type="subject">http://syriaca.org/person/67</idno>
                    <note type="type">person</note>
                    <note type="abstract">Metropolitan ‘of the East’, known as the Apostle of the
                        Arabs.<note/>
                    </note>
                </ab>
                <ab type="infobox">(d. 575) [<abbr>Syr. Orth.</abbr>]</ab>
                <div type="body">
                    <p>Metropolitan ‘of the East’, known as the Apostle of the Arabs. Originating
                        from <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Balad">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/42">Balad</placeName>
                        </ref>, he became first <abbr>bp.</abbr> of <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Beth-Arbaye">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/31">Beth ʿArbaye</placeName>
                        </ref>,
                        and was subsequently consecrated as Metropolitan of the East by <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Yaqub-Burdoyo">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/69">Yaʿqub
                            Burdʿoyo</persName>
                        </ref> (in 559). He undertook much missionary work, and it was
                        due to his conversion of a son of Khusrau I that he was eventually put to
                        death (2 Aug. 575). An informative biography, by an unknown author, is
                        preserved.</p>
                </div>
